"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 306px; height: 465px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    This technique has the advantage of causing minimal additional pain, and can be used with finger fractures or soft tissue injuries and lacerations. Cut one finger from a surgical glove to form a cylindrical sleeve. A) Place this sleeve on the involved digit and slip the proximal end circumferentially under the ring using a hemostat. B) Once in place, pull the proximal end back over the ring and toward the tip of the digit in a twisting motion, advancing the ring distally. Avoid pulling so hard that the glove rips or pulls out from under the ring.",
